    watchOutFor: "Don't log sensitive data — passwords, tokens, PII. Scrub them before logging. Also: /health and /ready are different: /health means 'the process is alive', /ready means 'ready to serve traffic'. Kubernetes uses both. A server can be healthy but not ready (still warming up cache).",
