    whyMatters: "Git hooks are scripts that run automatically before or after Git events (commit, push, merge). Pre-commit hooks let you enforce code quality locally — run linters, type checkers, tests — before bad code even enters the repo. Conventional Commits is a standardized format for commit messages (feat:, fix:, chore:) that lets you auto-generate changelogs and determine semantic version bumps. These are standard practices at any serious company.",
